# Naming Conventions

Match what already ships in the monorepo.

| Kind | Convention | Real example |
|---|---|---|
| Nest controller | `*.controller.ts` | `checkout.controller.ts` |
| Nest service | `*.service.ts` | `payment-fulfillment.service.ts` |
| Nest module | `*.module.ts` | `writer-payments.module.ts` |
| Scheduler | `*.scheduler.ts` | `assignment-due-reminder.scheduler.ts` |
| Prisma model → table | PascalCase → `@@map` snake | `Order` → `orders`, `totalPaise` → `total_paise` |
| React page/component | PascalCase file / export | `ArticleBody.tsx` |
| Hook | `useX.ts` | `useCart.ts` |
| Zod in `@inabiya/validation` | `camelCase` + `BodySchema` / `QuerySchema` | `checkoutPlaceOrderBodySchema`, `loginBodySchema` |
| Inferred type | Same stem without Schema | `CheckoutPlaceOrderBody` |
| Test | `*.spec.ts` / `*.test.ts` / `*.e2e.ts` | `place-order.spec.ts` |
| Env | SCREAMING_SNAKE | `JWT_ACCESS_SECRET` |
| `data-testid` | kebab-case | `checkout-pay-button` |
| Audit action | `resource.verb` dotted | `article.published`, `writer_payment.released` |

## Ubiquitous language (PRD)

Use: `GiftBox`, `InventoryItem`, `Article`, `SpecialistProfile`, `WriterPayment`, `CampaignProposal`, `ReverseBid`, `Deliverable`.

```text
❌ Student, Hostel, Exam, Admission, FeeInvoice, LibraryLoan
✅ ArticleStatus.MEDICAL_REVIEW, medicalGateRequired — not “creator review”
```

`Article.createdBy` relation is named `ArticleCreator` in Prisma — that means **editorial author**, not Creator Collective. Don’t conflate the two domains.

## HTTP paths

- Plural nouns under `/api/v1`: `/orders`, `/articles`, `/checkout/place-order` (command exception already used)
- No `/createOrder`-style verbs for CRUD resources
- Nest only when ownership is real: `/campaigns/:id/proposals`
